Acquisition path (LD#7 amended 2026-04-25 per Q1 verdict — Garage
upstream ships no Mac/Windows binary):

  * Linux (x86_64-musl, aarch64-musl):
      https://garagehq.deuxfleurs.fr/_releases/v2.3.0/<target>/garage
      Pinned SHA-256 per architecture (see versions.toml).

  * macOS:
      Homebrew formula `traylinx/tap/garagetytus` declares
      `depends_on "garage"`. The upstream `garage` formula compiles
      from the AGPL source tarball above (formula's own `sha256`
      declaration is the pin).

  * Windows:
      v0.1 prints a v0.2-deferral notice and exits 0. Reopens at
      v0.2 with explicit scope (build-our-own / WSL2 / drop).

Compliance posture:

  1. AGPL source-availability is satisfied at install time — the
     `garagetytus install` flow surfaces the upstream source URL
     before download.
  2. `garagetytus about` prints these values verbatim plus a path
     to this file.
  3. No `garage-*` Rust crate is ever imported, linked, or pulled
     in transitively. CI grep + cargo-deny enforce this on every PR
     (Phase B.4).

Other dependencies are direct Rust crates whose licenses are
recorded in the Cargo.toml `license` fields and tracked by
`cargo-deny`. None impose attribution requirements beyond what
their respective README/LICENSE files state.
